00:00:22,757 --> 00:00:25,892
narrator: today on "how it's made"...   

4
00:00:53,588 --> 00:00:56,188
in 2004, british scientists   

5
00:00:56,190 --> 00:00:59,659
extracted a substance      
called graphene from graphite,  

6
00:00:59,661 --> 00:01:02,394
which is the material used to make pencils.         

7
00:01:02,396 --> 00:01:05,064
they won the nobel prize for this discovery        

8
00:01:05,066 --> 00:01:07,933
and left their mark on physics history.       

9
00:01:07,935 --> 00:01:09,602
scientists continue to explore  

10
00:01:09,604 --> 00:01:12,238
graphene's extraordinary potential.            

11
00:01:14,275 --> 00:01:17,009
these silicon chips are dyed with thin flecks    

12
00:01:17,011 --> 00:01:19,612
of carbon, known as graphene.  

13
00:01:19,614 --> 00:01:21,948
just one atom thick and transparent,         

14
00:01:21,950 --> 00:01:26,351
graphene can sniff out chemicals in the air            

15
00:01:26,353 --> 00:01:28,821
and disease enzymes in blood.  

16
00:01:31,759 --> 00:01:35,293
this lab manufactures graphene using a process known      

17
00:01:35,295 --> 00:01:39,031
as chemical vapor deposition.  

18
00:01:39,033 --> 00:01:42,702
a technician loads a capsule  
containing a copper foil sheet  

19
00:01:42,704 --> 00:01:44,036
into a furnace.         

20
00:01:44,038 --> 00:01:46,439
he screws a cap on the end of the capsule    

21
00:01:46,441 --> 00:01:48,307
and shuts the furnace.      

22
00:01:48,309 --> 00:01:49,642
he activates a system      

23
00:01:49,644 --> 00:01:54,112
that uses argon gas to drive out oxygen.       

24
00:01:54,114 --> 00:01:57,182
when the furnace reaches about 1,800 degrees fahrenheit,           

25
00:01:57,184 --> 00:02:00,385
methane gas and hydrogen are added.            

26
00:02:00,387 --> 00:02:04,523
a reaction occurs that deposits graphene onto the foil.     

27
00:02:04,525 --> 00:02:09,327
graphene can't be seen with the naked eye.       

28
00:02:09,329 --> 00:02:12,064
a technician applies tiny gold contacts        

29
00:02:12,066 --> 00:02:13,666
to a silicon wafer        

30
00:02:13,668 --> 00:02:17,136
and then submerges it in solvent to rinse off the excess gold.  

31
00:02:17,138 --> 00:02:21,273
the remaining gold bits serve as electrical contacts.  

32
00:02:23,544 --> 00:02:27,413
a dip in acetone cleans off more of the loose flakes,    

33
00:02:27,415 --> 00:02:30,483
and a final rinse in alcohol removes the rest.   

34
00:02:36,557 --> 00:02:40,559
using a diamond-tip scribe, he scores the silicon wafer   

35
00:02:40,561 --> 00:02:42,428
and breaks it along the score lines,      

36
00:02:42,430 --> 00:02:44,964
creating rectangular chips.   

37
00:02:50,771 --> 00:02:52,771
another technician deposits liquid plastic     

38
00:02:52,773 --> 00:02:57,242
onto the transparent graphene on the copper foil.       

39
00:02:57,244 --> 00:03:00,846
he locks the foil in a machine called a spin coater.      

40
00:03:00,848 --> 00:03:03,382
it spins at 3,000 r.p.m.     

41
00:03:03,384 --> 00:03:04,850
this spreads the plastic     

42
00:03:04,852 --> 00:03:07,787
evenly across the graphene film on the foil.           

43
00:03:07,789 --> 00:03:12,057
it also accelerates the plastic's curing process.  

44
00:03:12,059 --> 00:03:15,060
he then separates the plastic-coated graphene   

45
00:03:15,062 --> 00:03:16,662
from the copper foil.      

46
00:03:16,664 --> 00:03:18,664
to do this,           

47
00:03:18,666 --> 00:03:22,334
he clips a wire to set of tweezers.       

48
00:03:22,336 --> 00:03:25,137
using the tweezers, he picks up a small piece    

49
00:03:25,139 --> 00:03:28,007
of the plastic, graphene, and copper sandwich       

50
00:03:28,009 --> 00:03:30,475
and plunges it in the water.   

51
00:03:30,477 --> 00:03:33,746
the tweezers apply an electrical charge through the copper,    

52
00:03:33,748 --> 00:03:36,282
causing bubbles to form in the water.      

53
00:03:36,284 --> 00:03:38,216
these bubbles lift the graphene            

54
00:03:38,218 --> 00:03:40,953
and plastic film away from the copper.      

55
00:03:40,955 --> 00:03:45,691
the graphene now clings only to the plastic backing.   

56
00:03:45,693 --> 00:03:48,360
he scoops the plastic-backed graphene square         

57
00:03:48,362 --> 00:03:51,897
out of the water using a large piece of plastic.    

58
00:03:51,899 --> 00:03:53,232
to remove contaminants,     

59
00:03:53,234 --> 00:03:56,969
he immerses the square in a series of solutions.    

60
00:03:56,971 --> 00:03:58,304
in the last solution,      

61
00:03:58,306 --> 00:04:00,839
he slides the square off the carrier.         

62
00:04:00,841 --> 00:04:03,509
and the square floats freely.  

63
00:04:03,511 --> 00:04:06,245
he picks up the silicon chip with tweezers          

64
00:04:06,247 --> 00:04:09,181
and uses it to retrieve the floating graphene      

65
00:04:09,183 --> 00:04:12,584
and plastic square.       

66
00:04:12,586 --> 00:04:15,154
it now sits on the silicon chip.              

67
00:04:19,126 --> 00:04:20,792
after taping metal stencils   

68
00:04:20,794 --> 00:04:23,395
over three of the graphene-covered chips,   

69
00:04:23,397 --> 00:04:25,931
he suspends them above gold pellets        

70
00:04:25,933 --> 00:04:28,801
in a machine known as the evaporator.         

71
00:04:33,007 --> 00:04:36,776
he closes the evaporator, then turns up the heat.     

72
00:04:41,816 --> 00:04:43,882
a vacuum pulls the gold toward the stencils       

73
00:04:43,884 --> 00:04:46,051
as it evaporates.        

74
00:04:48,288 --> 00:04:50,689
the gold and exposed graphene  

75
00:04:50,691 --> 00:04:53,692
adhere to one another as they cool and solidify.    

76
00:04:53,694 --> 00:04:56,361
the technician removes the stencils from the chips,   

77
00:04:56,363 --> 00:04:58,430
revealing gold horizontal runners        

78
00:04:58,432 --> 00:05:01,233
between the gold contacts.    

79
00:05:01,235 --> 00:05:04,436
he transfers the chip to a plasma etcher.       

80
00:05:04,438 --> 00:05:05,771
he activates the chip,      

81
00:05:05,773 --> 00:05:08,307
and plasma gas floods the chamber.       

82
00:05:08,309 --> 00:05:12,845
the gas strips off any graphene that's not protected by gold.  

83
00:05:12,847 --> 00:05:14,446
only the gold contacts      

84
00:05:14,448 --> 00:05:18,116
and gold-covered graphene runners remain on the chip.   

85
00:05:18,118 --> 00:05:20,519
solvent dissolves the plastic backing       

86
00:05:20,521 --> 00:05:22,321
on the graphene runners,     

87
00:05:22,323 --> 00:05:26,658
taking the protective gold with it, leaving only graphene.            

88
00:05:26,660 --> 00:05:31,529
the technician now has a graphene sensor chip.   

89
00:05:31,531 --> 00:05:33,866
it's time to test its sensory powers    

90
00:05:33,868 --> 00:05:37,069
using antibodies        
for a certain disease protein.  

91
00:05:37,071 --> 00:05:41,473
the antibodies attach to the surface of the graphene.            

92
00:05:41,475 --> 00:05:43,475
she tests the signal from the chip          

93
00:05:43,477 --> 00:05:47,746
to confirm that it reads the protein correctly.           

94
00:05:47,748 --> 00:05:50,482
this graphene chip is ready to act         

95
00:05:50,484 --> 00:05:52,852
as a high-tech sixth sense.   

